pe=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Mel=
inda Jamieson</a> </span></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
KD_3</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong><span><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-succes=
s">CLOSED</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-08" class=3D"date-past">08 May 2025</time></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Post MVP when Dual or N Auth model is applicable, should the individual cum=
ulative validation &amp; deduction happen only for the final checker approv=
al or at the time of each respective checker approval??</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Individual cumulative limit should be validate &amp; deducted for each indi=
vidual checker approval, whereas the organisation channel cumulative limit =
should only be validated and deducted at the time of final checker approval=
.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span data-teams=3D"true"><span class=3D"fui-StyledText ___rj1mvc0 fyind=
8e f1k6fduh fdvs7vj fx5ovu0"><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" =
data-username=3D"F069184" href=3D"/display/~F069184" data-linked-resource-i=
d=3D"701241880" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-typ=
e=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Priy=
anka Sonaganti</a>&nbsp;<br></span></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
KD_4</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong><span><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-succes=
s">CLOSED</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-08" class=3D"date-past">08 May 2025</time></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Will the individual checker cumulative limit &amp; organisation channel =
cumulative limit be replenished in case of,</p>
<ul>
<li>Payment processing failure when the payment is submitted for processing=
</li>
<li>Workflow approval failure when the payment request is submitted for app=
roval to DSR after limits check</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
For MVP the payment limits will not be replenished, however, for MMP, the l=
imits will be replenished accordingly</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span data-teams=3D"true"><span class=3D"fui-StyledText ___rj1mvc0 fyind=
8e f1k6fduh fdvs7vj fx5ovu0"><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" =
data-username=3D"F071119" href=3D"/display/~F071119" data-linked-resource-i=
d=3D"847097206" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-typ=
e=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Dipi=
ka Guruprasad</a></span></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
KD_5</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong><span><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-succes=
s">CLOSED</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-06-27" class=3D"date-past">27 Jun 2025</time></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Should the two new routes to GET payment limits and to VALIDATE the paym=
ent limits be exposed from maker-checker Widget Exp API rather than from Pa=
yment MFE Exp API?? From re-usability perspective(if payment limits will be=
 applicable for staff in the future), these routes could be reused for staf=
f if they are exposed from maker-checker Widget Exp API.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
For now, it is not clear on the payment limits requirement for staff(if at =
all they will be applicable for staff &amp; if yes, when and how), so based=
 on the information available at hand, it is decided to expose these routes=
 from Payment MFE Exp API as the payment limits are purely applicable for c=
ustomers alone when this decision was made.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span data-teams=3D"true"><span class=3D"fui-StyledText ___rj1mvc0 fyind=
8e f1k6fduh fdvs7vj fx5ovu0"><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" =
data-username=3D"M064309" href=3D"/display/~M064309" data-linked-resource-i=
d=3D"1898146614" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-ty=
pe=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Unk=
nown User (m064309)</a>&nbsp;<br></span></span></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-RAID-(R)isk,(A)ssumptions,(I)ssuesand(D=
)ependencies">RAID<span>&nbsp;</span>- (R)isk, (A)ssumptions, (I)ssues and =
(D)ependencies</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable" data-snooker-col-series=3D"numbers=
" data-snooker-locked-cols=3D"0">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"">
<col class=3D"">
<col>
<col class=3D"">
<col class=3D"">
<col class=3D"">
<col class=3D"">
