<thead class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false"><br></t=
h>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Type</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Status</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Date&nbsp;</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Description</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Impact</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Mitigation</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Owner</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p>Remarks</p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false">1</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
D</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong><span><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-succes=
s">CLOSED</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-08" class=3D"date-past">08 May 2025</time></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Payments Limit CAP API to,</p>
<ul>
<li>Get the Checker transaction &amp; daily cumulative limit</li>
<li><s>Get <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"934402c5-d1d9-=
4b9a-8440-c53c9931e587">NPP transaction limit &amp; DE trans</span>action l=
imit</s></li>
<li>Get the Checker remaining daily cumulative limit</li>
<li>Get the Organisation Channel daily Cumulative limit</li>
<li>Get the remaining Organisation Channel daily Cumulative limit</li>
<li>Validate Payment Limits(Checker transaction limit, NPP Tx limit, DE Tx =
limit, Checker Cumulative Limit &amp; Organisation Channel Cumulative Limit=
) when a workflow is being approved by a Checker.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Without this CAP API, Payment Limits requirements cannot be implemented for=
 Channels.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Payments Team</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false">2</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
D</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong><span><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-succes=
s">CLOSED</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-05-08" class=3D"date-past">08 May 2025</time></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Following validations should be performed when processing the payments a=
nd appropriate error(with specific error code) should be returned by the Pa=
yment Initiation API if any of the following validation fails as part of pa=
yment processing,</p>
<ul>
<li>Treasury Limit validati<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"1a5cb4d6-96a9-4ab7-84cc-519b1b3a8aa1">on &amp; error</span></li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"1a5cb4d6-96a9-4ab7-84=
cc-519b1b3a8aa1">Unique instruction trace id validation &amp; error(this is=
 to ensure the Payment Limits validations are done successfully as part of =
Checker app</span>roval)</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Without this, W1C Channels will not be able to identify and handle specific=
 error scenarios. Also, without the Unique transaction trace id validation,=
 there is a risk of bypassing the Checker validation in case of any vulnera=
bility attack.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Payments Team</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false">3</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
D&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong><span><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-succes=
s">CLOSED</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-06-05" class=3D"date-past">05 Jun 2025</time></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>Entitlements to expose the capability to query and fetch user's CIS Key =
based on the IAM ID/Guid as read from access_token in the <span class=3D"in=
line-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"455981f6-e489-42be-9669-abce61d13e12">Exp<=
/span>&nbsp;API</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
In the Payment Limits DB, the Payment Limits are maintained against Organis=
ation CISKey and User's CISKey, so when getting and validating the Payment =
Limits for channels, user's and Organisation CISKey should be passed in the=
 request body to Payment Limits CAP API, so <span class=3D"inline-comment-m=
arker" data-ref=3D"2ba98e74-fc06-4406-bd00-2373d06bbfa6">without</span> the=
 CISKey channels will not be able to call Payment Limits CAP API</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>Entitlements</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M058894" =
href=3D"/display/~M058894" data-linked-resource-id=3D"709545411" data-linke=
d-resource-version=3D"3" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-u=
rl=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Jeslin Cyriac</a> <a class=3D"=
confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M063113" href=3D"/displa=
y/~M063113" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1697757305" data-linked-resource-ver=
sion=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"https://=
confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Unknown User (m063113)</a>&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>As part of Nov 2025 ERM, logged in user's CISKey will be exposed from ac=
cess_token under "userId" attribute, so channels will read the user's CISKe=
y from the access_token in the Exp API. Organisation CISKey will be passed =
to the Exp API(from the UI) as a protected request header "protected-orgId"=
, so channels will read the same from the request header in the Exp API.</p=
>
<p>ACD link &amp; screenshot highlighting the user's CISKey in access_token=
 : <a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1872559006">ACD - W1 User Man=
agement &amp; Authentication</a></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"91" src=3D"0cbe0c364a7fdcc7ee11173c2ba31100f62ad413f57978d4c9b188d1f10=
6bc98" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/2020673375/image-2025-7-3_10=
-24-12.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1751502252413&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"2085383298" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-2025-7-3_10-24-12.png" data-bas=
e-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"2020673375" data-=
linked-resource-container-version=3D"174" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p=
>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false">4</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
D</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><strong><span><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-succes=
s">CLOSED</span></span></strong></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-06-05" class=3D"date-past">05 Jun 2025</time></p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>As part of Checker approval, the payment limits will be validate and ded=
ucted as part of a single Payment Limits CAP API call, so even before the p=
ayment limits are validated, user's Entitlements(Authorise_Payment) &amp; M=
FA should be completed successfully, else the payment limits will be deduct=
ed even if a user has lost the entitlements or MFA is unsuccessful(if the p=
ayment limits validation is done prior to Entitlements check &amp; MFA). As=
 part of MVP, any payment limits deducted will not be replenished, so to av=
oid deducting the payment limits incorrectly, Entitlements check &amp; MFA =
should be completed even before the payment limits are validated for a chec=
ker(refer to this sequence flow below for details&nbsp;<a href=3D"#SD:Payme=
ntsLimitsChannels-PaymentLimitsflowaspartofCheckerApproval">PaymentLimitsfl=
owaspartofCheckerApproval</a>)</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
The payment limits will be deducted incorrectly in case user has lost the e=
ntitlement or MFA is unsuccessful.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<ul>
<li>Channels team</li>
<li>Entitlements team&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M058894" =
href=3D"/display/~M058894" data-linked-resource-id=3D"709545411" data-linke=
d-resource-version=3D"3" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-u=
rl=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Jeslin Cyriac</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"M063113" =
href=3D"/display/~M063113" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1697757305" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Unknown User (m063113)</a>&nb=
sp;</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
