<h1 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-SolutionOverview"><span>Solution Overvi=
ew</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-UserInterfaces"><span>User Interfaces</=
span></h2>
<p><span>Payments Limit related UX changes:&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link"=
 href=3D"https://dstsb2.axshare.com/#id=3D35xewc&amp;p=3D3_0_payments_list&=
amp;g=3D1" rel=3D"nofollow">U</a>X Link TBD</span></p>
<h2 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-SequenceDiagram"><span>Sequence Diagram=
</span></h2>
<h3 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-PaymentsMFEandPaymentsExpAPI-UniqueInst=
ructionTraceId"><span>Payments MFE and Payments Exp API - Unique <span styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Instruction Trace Id</span></span></h3>
<p><span>As part of Payment Limits, UUID(unique <span style=3D"color: rgb(2=
3,43,77);">I<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"4f0258e5-ede3=
-47a5-97c0-9ec50424cf58">nstructio</span>n Trace Id)</span> will have to be=
 generated in the Payments MFE and the same will have to be passed as part =
of POST /payments request and also the same unique identifier will have to =
be passed to the Payment Limits CAP API as part of payment limits validatio=
n at the time of checker approval. This unique identifier will be validated=
 at the time of payment processing to verify if the payment limits check wa=
s carried out using the same unique identifier at the time of checker appro=
val. The payment processing will fail in case of any mismatch in the valida=
tion.<u><strong> <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">Please Note:</span></=
strong></u><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"> The Instruction Trace Id v=
alidation at the time of payment processing will be applicable to "customer=
" submitted payments alone and for "staff" submitted payments, so Payment I=
nitiation CAP API will determine if the Payment was submitted by "customer"=
 or "staff" based on x-consumerType request header that will be populated/p=
ropagated from Payments Exp API to Payment Initiation CAP API when payment =
is submitted for processing. The Payment Initiation CAP API will validate t=
he Instruction Trace Id against the Payment Limits enforcement check only i=
f&nbsp;x-consumerType request header is "customer".&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></spa=
n></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span> <map id=3D"gliffy-map-2038174127-7113" name=3D"gliffy-map-2038174=
127-7113"></map> </span></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<table class=3D"gliffy-macro-inner-table">
<caption align=3D"bottom">
</caption>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img style=3D"border: none; width: 1399px;" usemap=3D"#gliffy-map-20381=
74127-7113" src=3D"b5487224b678f1c5858e6191f3b11a077c82fcb3cdf68049c3e8a7a3=
b71ddf79" alt=3D"" class=3D"gliffy-macro-image" width=3D"468" height=3D"416=
"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-PaymentLimitsflowaspartofCheckerApprova=
l"><span>Payment Limits flow as part of Checker Approval</span></h3>
<p><span>The payment limits will be validated and deducted from the respect=
ive cumulative limits at the time of payment request workflow approval. Whe=
n a checker is approving the payment workflow request as part of maker-chec=
ker process, Channels will explicitly call Payment Limits CAP API to valida=
te the payment limits(<u><strong>note:</strong></u> as part of the payment =
limits validation call, the payment limits will be deduct from the respecti=
ve cumulative limits if the limits are not reached). The Payment workflow r=
equest will be submitted for approval to DSR(via Entitlements) only if the =
Payment Limits are not reached. If payment limits are reached, appropriate =
error message will be displayed to checkers(at the time of approval) indica=
ting which specific limits are reached and the payment workflow request wil=
l not be submitted for approval(the request will re<span class=3D"inline-co=
mment-marker" data-ref=3D"99208b93-afc5-4d99-b370-b12f52f86c93">main in the=
 que</span>ue for approval).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span>The following sequence diagram will indicate the sequence flow app=
licable for Channels.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Refer to the follo<span cl=
ass=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"9b5a0f0b-6b7c-4e7b-832a-2c18f9e4b=
86e">wing API docu</span>mentation for API related details:</span></strong>=
</p>
<ul>
<li><span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/ex=
p-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalaxypaymentv2-GET/paymentLimits">exp-galaxy-paymen=
t-v2#GET/paymentLimits</a></span></span></li>
<li><span><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/ex=
p-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/validatePaymentLimits">exp-gala=
xy-payment-v2#POST/validatePaymentLimits</a></span></span></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><span> <map id=3D"gliffy-map-2029131103-7285" name=3D"gliffy-map-2029131=
103-7285"></map> </span></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<table class=3D"gliffy-macro-inner-table">
<caption align=3D"bottom">
</caption>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img style=3D"border: none; width: 3164px;" usemap=3D"#gliffy-map-20291=
31103-7285" src=3D"2df024c70e7ac6c0032f165d0b0da19c600e3e22fa0144cebd1f9540=
37e8a1a7" alt=3D"" class=3D"gliffy-macro-image" width=3D"468" height=3D"563=
"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p></p>
<p><br></p>
<h4 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-Errorhandling1:ValidatePaymentLimitsExp=
APIerrorresponsewhenoneormorelimitsarebreached">Error handling 1: Validate =
Payment Limits Exp API error response when one or more limits are breached<=
/h4>
<p>Following Validate Payment Limits Exp API response will be returned if o=
ne or more payment limits are breached(Exp API SD can be found here: <a hre=
f=3D"/display/ARTC/exp-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/validatePa=
ymentLimits">exp-galaxy-payment-v2#POST/validatePaymentLimits</a>)</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">http sta=
tus code: 200
{
    "entities": {
        "validatePaymentLimits": [
            {
               "isSuccess": false,
               "code": 2302,
               "message": "Limit breaches for user transaction amount",
               "details": "Settlement amount must be lower than the user's =
maximum transaction limit {limitValue}"
            },
            {
               "isSuccess": false,
               "code": 2303,
               "message": "Limit breaches for user daily amount",
               "details": "Settlement amount must be lower than the user's =
maximum daily limit {limitValue}"
            },
            {
               "isSuccess": false,
               "code": 2304,
               "message": "Limit breaches for organisation channel daily am=
ount",
               "details": "Settlement amount must be lower than the Organis=
ation Channel's maximum daily limit {limitValue}"
            },
            {
               "isSuccess": false,
               "code": 2305,
               "message": "Limit breaches for scheme  transaction amount",
               "details": "Settlement amount must be lower than  scheme's m=
aximum  transaction limit {limitValue}"
            }
        ]
    },
    "result": {
        "validatePaymentLimits": [
            "5ab2ba7e-8f5f-45dc-9bc6-0d18ffb53c2e",
            "5ab2ba7e-8f5f-45dc-9bc6-0d18ffb53c2f",
            "5ab2ba7e-8f5f-45dc-9bc6-0d18ffb53c2g",
            "5ab2ba7e-8f5f-45dc-9bc6-0d18ffb53c2h"
        ]
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h4 id=3D"SD:PaymentsLimitsChannels-Errorhandling2:PaymentInitiationCAPAPIr=
esponserelatedtoPaymentLimitserrorsaspartofPaymentProcessing"><span class=
=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"899242bd-4683-4f5e-9d90-4f83686a5170=
">Error handling 2</span>:&nbsp;Payment Initiation CAP API response related=
 to Payment Limits errors as part of Payment Processing</h4>
<p>Following Payment Initiation CAP API response will be returned to the co=
nsumers when the payment processing is failed due to payment limits validat=
ion errors. The corresponding POST /payments Exp API response can be found =
here: <a href=3D"/display/ARTC/exp-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalaxypaymentv2-POS=
T/payments">exp-galaxy-payment-v2#POST/payments</a>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">1. Verif=
ication of payment limit check failed
http status code: 201
{
    "data": {
        "paymentStatusReport": {
            "paymentInformation": {
                "paymentInformationStatus": "RJCT",
                "statusReasonInformation": [
                    {
                        "reason": "ExternalValidationEnrichmentFailed",
                        "additionalInformation": "TBC"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    }
}

2. Treasury check failed due to FSS unavailability
http status code: 201
{
    "data": {
        "paymentStatusReport": {
            "paymentInformation": {
                "paymentInformationStatus": "RJCT",
                "statusReasonInformation": [
                    {
                        "reason": "ExternalValidationEnrichmentFailed",
                        "additionalInformation": "AM24"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    }
}

3. Treasury check failed due to amount exceeded the treasury limit
http status code: 201
{
    "data": {
        "paymentStatusReport": {
            "paymentInformation": {
                "paymentInformationStatus": "RJCT",
                "statusReasonInformation": [
                    {
                        "reason": "ExternalValidationEnrichmentFailed",
                        "additionalInformation": "AM23"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
